Q5: Comile time error vs Runtime error 

 Comile time error : when there is a mistake in the code that the compiler catches before the program 
	                     runs like syntax error,missing refrences. the program would not
						 run until you fix these errors.
						 compile time error is not exception.
 Runtime error : this error occurs while the code is running .the code might be correct but something
                     unexpected occur during the execution like dividing by zero these error cause 
                     the program to crash or behave unexpectedly. this is called run time error.
					 Runtime error is exception 
					 
	
    Compile-time errors → detected by compiler.
    Runtime errors → happen while program runs.	
 
Q6: Checked exception vs Unchecked exception
 
 Checked exception / compile time excetion : 
    checked exception can be checked by compiler. if some code within the method throws the checked 
	exception then the method must handel the exception(using try-catch block) or it must specify the 
	exception using throws keyword
	ex : file not found , class not found.
	
	or another defination  
	
	 These are exceptions that the compiler checks at compile time. You must handle them using a try-catch block
	 or declare them in the method signature using throws. For example, IOException and SQLException are checked 
	 exceptions.
	 
	 or this is good explaination  
	 
	  exception occur during the compilation time(.java file into .class file) is called checked exception.
	 This means that the compiler checks for these exceptions when compiling the .java file into a .class file, 
	 and requires you to either catch them or declare them using the throws keyword.
	 
	
	code  : 
	try{
	   //code that may cause an exception 
	}catch{
	   //handel the exception
	}
	
	
 
 Unchecked exception / run time excetion :
    unchecked exception are the exception which are not checked at compile time and it can be handel 
    with in try-catch block.
	
	or
	
	These are exceptions that the compiler does not check at compile time. They happen during runtime and are 
	usually caused by programming errors like NullPointerException or ArithmeticException. You don’t have to 
	handle them explicitly.you can handel unchecked exception using try catch block and by declaring throws 
	keyword with method signature.

    or this is good explanation  
	
	 exception occur during the runtime time(.class file into machine code) is called uncheked exception.
	 
	
    ex  :arithemetic, null pointer ,arrayindex out of bound,number format exception 	
                 
 
  Note :   
  wrong concept  : compile time exception occurs at compile time and run time exception occurs at 
                   run time 
  correct concept : all the exception occurs at run time.  				   
	  
