Q17 : can we use multiple catch block  ? 
Ans : Yes, you can use multiple catch blocks with a single try block in Java. This allows you to handle different
      types of exceptions separately , but here order must be from child exception to parent exception. 
	  
	  code  : 
	    try {
			// Code that may throw different exceptions
		} catch (NullPointerException e) {
			System.out.println("Caught NullPointerException");
		} catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
			System.out.println("Caught ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException");
		} catch (Exception e) {
			System.out.println("Caught generic Exception");
		}

